alert.note: Alert for Coastal Dixie; Coastal Taylor (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued September 10 at 4:33AM EDT until September 10 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM EDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Coastal flood advisory in effect for minor coastal flooding. * WHERE...Coastal Taylor and Coastal Dixie Counties. * WHEN...Until 6 PM EDT this evening. Peak water levels are expected around the time of high tide, which will be around 230 pm EDT this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Peak water levels up to 2 feet above ground level are expected around the time of high tide. At these levels, the boat ramps in Keaton Beach and Steinhatchee will flood. In Horseshoe Beach, water will begin to overtop the rocks at the end of Main Street. In Suwannee, several areas will experience minor flooding as water rises over the tops of the canals.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
